<font color="#FF0000">LETTING GO</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec 14 13:53:56 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
My Vietnam past follows me around at times like a lost puppy and at times like a case of the flu.<br><br>
My Vietnam time capsule is as bound to me as I am to it, because part of me remains locked inside.<br><br>
I feel it is not possible to let go of this past in the sense of denial. In the sense of acknowlegement and accomodation, I can let pass away of some of the present effects of my Vietnam past, but the memories will be with me forever.<br><br>
(This is a topic that is tough at the core. I would be interested in reading comments on this from some of the protestors whose attachments to the past appear as strong as mine, though with a different point of view.) 
